\pard\b 1. Purpose of This Document\b0\par
\par
\pard This document is submitted for formal client review, approval, and sign-off of the CRII / EagleTV mobile application. It provides a professional summary of the implemented platform scope, key features, core functionalities, administrative controls, and operational modules delivered as part of the application.\par
\par
\pard The purpose of this sign-off is to confirm that the client has reviewed the application scope and accepts the delivered functionality in line with the agreed business objectives, user workflows, and operational expectations.\par
\par
\pard\b 2. Solution Overview\b0\par
\par
\pard CRII / EagleTV is a role-based mobile application built to support content publishing, controlled information distribution, user engagement, administrative moderation, and operational communication workflows. The platform is designed for structured content delivery and management, with separate access and privileges for public users, reporters/content creators, and administrators.\par
\par
\pard The application supports content viewing, content creation, moderation, user management, reporting, multilingual usage, notifications, meetings coordination, and emergency alert communication within a single unified system.\par
\par
\pard\b 3. Platform Scope\b0\par
\par
\pard 1. User onboarding and secure login\par
2. OTP-based authentication\par
3. Role-based access control\par
4. News/content feed consumption\par
5. Rich content creation and publishing workflow\par
6. Approval and moderation management\par
7. Search and discovery tools\par
8. User profile and account management\par
9. Notifications and user communication\par
10. Emergency alerts management\par
11. Meetings management\par
12. Reports generation and document export\par
13. Department linkage and quick-access information\par
14. Settings, language, and personalization controls\par
\par
\pard\b 4. Detailed Features and Functionalities\b0\par
\par
\pard\b 4.1 User Onboarding and Authentication\b0\par
\par
\pard The application includes a guided onboarding and login experience intended to make first-time access simple and secure.\par
\par
\pard Included functionality:\par
- Introductory onboarding screens explaining the purpose and value of the application\par
- Login method selection flow\par
- OTP-based phone number authentication\par
- OTP verification and resend workflow\par
- Secure account resolution through backend authentication\par
- Persistent user session handling to reduce repeated login effort\par
- Splash/loading flow to validate user session and initialize services at startup\par
\par
\pard Business value:\par
- Provides secure access control\par
- Minimizes login friction for end users\par
- Supports a streamlined sign-in process for mobile-first audiences\par
\par
\pard\b 4.2 Role-Based Access Control\b0\par
\par
\pard The platform is structured around user roles so that each user sees only the functions relevant to their responsibilities.\par
\par
\pard Roles supported:\par
- Admin / Super Admin\par
- Reporter / Content Creator\par
- Public User\par
\par
\pard Role functionality:\par
- Admin users can manage content approval, user operations, analytics, and system-level operational modules\par
- Reporter users can create and submit content for review\par
- Public users can consume approved content and interact with available public-facing features\par
\par
\pard\b 4.3 Content Feed and Content Consumption\b0\par
\par
\pard The application provides a modern feed experience for viewing published content in an engaging mobile-friendly format.\par
\par
\pard Included functionality:\par
- Home feed for approved content\par
- Smooth page-based or card-based browsing experience\par
- Support for multiple content formats including text, image, video, PDF, article, story, and poetry-style entries\par
- Post detail view for expanded reading\par
- Dedicated article reading experience\par
- In-app PDF viewing\par
- Video playback support\par
- Breaking news highlight support\par
- Category-based browsing for faster navigation\par
\par
\pard User interaction functionality:\par
- Like posts\par
- Bookmark/save posts\par
- Share posts\par
- View detailed post information and associated metadata\par
\par
\pard\b 4.4 Content Creation and Publishing Workflow\b0\par
\par
\pard The application includes a complete content submission workflow for authorized users.\par
\par
\pard Included functionality:\par
- Create post screen for authorized users\par
- Support for text-only posts\par
- Support for image posts\par
- Support for video posts\par
- Support for PDF/document-based posts\par
- Support for article, story, and poetry formats\par
- Category assignment during content creation\par
- Caption and description management\par
- Media selection and preview\par
- Editing of created content before submission\par
- Post update/edit workflow\par
- Rejected post correction and resubmission workflow\par
\par
\pard Workflow logic:\par
- Admin-created posts may be published directly based on permissions\par
- Reporter-created posts move into pending review until approved\par
- Rejected posts can be edited and resubmitted for approval\par
\par
\pard\b 4.5 Content Moderation and Approval Management\b0\par
\par
\pard A dedicated moderation and approval mechanism is included for administrative oversight.\par
\par
\pard Included functionality:\par
- Pending, approved, and rejected post tracking\par
- Approve post action\par
- Reject post action with rejection reason\par
- Delete post controls where authorized\par
- All-posts management view for moderators\par
- Rejected-post recovery and resubmission handling\par
- Pending count visibility for moderators\par
- Audit-oriented status changes across the publishing lifecycle\par
\par
\pard\b 4.6 Search and Discovery\b0\par
\par
\pard The application includes search and discovery tools to improve content visibility and user navigation.\par
\par
\pard Included functionality:\par
- Search across available content\par
- Search for users\par
- Category discovery\par
- Hashtag-based exploration\par
- Trending and discoverability components\par
- Search history support for better user convenience\par
\par
\pard\b 4.7 Profile and Account Management\b0\par
\par
\pard Each user is provided with a profile section for managing personal and published information.\par
\par
\pard Included functionality:\par
- Profile screen\par
- Edit profile workflow\par
- Basic details management\par
- Profile statistics display\par
- Posts listing and grid display\par
- Bookmarked content view\par
- User-specific content tracking\par
\par
\pard\b 4.8 Notifications and Communication\b0\par
\par
\pard The application includes an integrated notification module for system communication and engagement.\par
\par
\pard Included functionality:\par
- Notification center and list view\par
- Push notification integration readiness\par
- Notification preference handling\par
- Background notification handling support\par
- Deletion and management of notifications\par
\par
\pard\b 4.9 Meetings Management\b0\par
\par
\pard The application includes a meetings management module for organizing structured events or sessions.\par
\par
\pard Included functionality:\par
- Meetings list for end users\par
- Meetings management module for authorized users\par
- Create meeting\par
- Edit meeting\par
- Status tracking for upcoming, ongoing, completed, and cancelled meetings\par
- Interested user tracking\par
- Venue and scheduling details\par
\par
\pard\b 4.10 Emergency Alerts Module\b0\par
\par
\pard The platform includes emergency communication capability for urgent announcements.\par
\par
\pard Included functionality:\par
- Emergency alerts listing\par
- Emergency alert creation for authorized users\par
- Alert title and message handling\par
- Alert distribution workflow within the application\par
\par
\pard\b 4.11 Reports and Document Export\b0\par
\par
\pard The application includes a reporting area for generating and viewing structured reports.\par
\par
\pard Included functionality:\par
- Reports list screen\par
- Report detail view\par
- Report creation workflow\par
- Draft save functionality\par
- PDF export support\par
- Print support for generated reports\par
\par
\pard\b 4.12 User Management and Administrative Controls\b0\par
\par
\pard The platform includes administrative control features for managing user accounts and permissions.\par
\par
\pard Included functionality:\par
- User management screen\par
- Search and review of users\par
- Add user workflow\par
- Role update and change workflow\par
- Controlled delete user action\par
- Restricted role escalation logic for privileged operations\par
- Storage limits management\par
- Reporter analytics view\par
- General analytics dashboard\par
- Audit timeline visibility\par
\par
\pard\b 4.13 Department Linkages and Quick Access Information\b0\par
\par
\pard The application includes a department linkage section to provide structured access to important departmental contacts and service references.\par
\par
\pard Included functionality:\par
- Department linkage screen\par
- Emergency number access\par
- Police department reference\par
- Revenue department reference\par
- Legal aid reference\par
- Health and welfare reference\par
\par
\pard\b 4.14 Settings, Language, and Personalization\b0\par
\par
\pard The application includes settings and personalization controls to improve usability and accommodate different user preferences.\par
\par
\pard Included functionality:\par
- Application settings screen\par
- Language preference management\par
- Multi-language support\par
- Theme handling\par
- Notification timing and quiet hours preferences\par
- Logout and account session controls\par
\par
\pard\b 4.15 Technical and Operational Characteristics\b0\par
\par
\pard In addition to user-facing functionality, the solution includes core operational capabilities that support stability, scalability, and maintainability.\par
\par
\pard Included characteristics:\par
- Firebase-based backend integration\par
- Backend-driven user role resolution\par
- Firestore data handling and access rules\par
- Callable backend functions for secure actions\par
- Local cache usage for faster response\par
- Connectivity-aware behavior\par
- Background processing support for selected operations\par
- Error capture and crash monitoring support\par
- Media caching and media thumbnail generation support\par
\par
\pard\b 5. Acceptance Statement\b0\par
\par
\pard By signing this document, the client confirms that:\par
- The delivered application modules and workflows have been reviewed\par
- The listed features and functionalities represent the agreed delivery scope for this approval stage\par
- The application is accepted in its present delivered form, subject to any mutually documented observations, minor revisions, or post-approval enhancement items\par
- Any future change requests outside this approved scope may be treated as a separate enhancement or maintenance activity\par
